Vice President Biden announced that his longtime aide and Press Secretary, Elizabeth Alexander, will be leaving at the end of May to practice law. She will be replaced by Kendra Barkoff, who most recently served as Secretary of the Interior Ken Salazar's Deputy Communications Director and Press Secretary. Vice President Biden praised Alexander for her dedication and professionalism, while expressing excitement for Barkoff to join the team. Barkoff brings extensive communications and press experience, having worked as a press secretary for Senator Bob Casey and in various other roles for senators Richard Durbin and Maria Cantwell. She will join the Vice President's communications office, led by Communications Director Shailagh Murray, Deputy Press Secretary Amy Dudley, and Assistant Press Secretary Liz Allen, starting in June.